[...] Monitoring, alerts and triage signals


Primary signals produced by FERS:

- SLI delta per-anchor (numerical): stored as time-series metric ers.anchor.delta_{probe_name}
- Schema violation rate (percentage) ers.schema.violation_{model}_{schema}
- Tool fallback increment ers.tool.fallback_delta_{model}
- Reproducibility score (0-1): fraction of injected failures that reproduce across seeds (low score indicates non-deterministic failure)

[...]    - context_length_profile: distribution (mean, 90p)


Example template (YAML excerpt):
| id: booking-nested-3step
| description: user searches, asks clarifying q, then books with payment fragment
| intents:
|   - { name: search, p: 0.45 }
|   - { name: clarify, p: 0.35 }
|   - { name: confirm_payment, p: 0.20 }

[...] 7) Upload artifacts: raw responses, latency histograms, token counters, and cost model inputs to `s3://redwood-evals/results/<run-id>/`.


Key metrics to collect (labels map to Prometheus metrics):
- request_duration_seconds{quantization,profile,model_version} (Histogram)
- token_generated_count_total{model_variant}
- kv_cache_hit_ratio{profile}
- batch_size_distribution{profile}
- gpu_utilization_percent{node}
- runtime_fallback_count_total (counter)
